						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of gold and a lamp-stand for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirumūlaṭṭāṉattu-Perumāṉaḍigaḷ at Tirunalakkuṉṟam in Kuṉṟiyūr nāḍu, by <hi rend="bold">Śaṅkaraṉ Kuṉṟappoḻāṉ</hi> (mentioned in No. 363 above) a native of Malai-nāḍu. This is probably an inscription of Parāntaka whose epigraph of the same regnal year (No. 351 of 1904) and in the same writing is engraved below this record.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
